# Session handoff

**File:** `PM/session-handoff.md` (same path as `pm/session-handoff.md` on Windows). **Always** update it at the end of every scoped task — never leave a stale handoff when reporting work complete.

At the end of **every scoped task** (feature, fix, deploy, or doc-only wrap-up):

1. Edit `PM/session-handoff.md` — baseline (branch, commit, prod/build), what shipped, blockers, next actions.
2. Run `.\scripts\update-session-handoff.ps1` after deploys (or use a deploy script below) so baseline matches HEAD and production build metadata.
3. Do not mark the task done with a stale handoff or an old baseline commit.

Deploy paths that refresh baseline (and commit handoff when it changed):

- `PM\Deploy-popuphub.bat` or `.\scripts\deploy-popuphub.ps1` (works from Explorer, cmd, or PowerShell)
- `.\scripts\ship.ps1 -Message "..."`

Agents still must edit narrative sections (goal, smoke-test, next actions) when they change; the script only refreshes baseline and last-deploy metadata.
